#
#
#


#### Dr. Melissa Horger is currently a postdoctoral reserach in the Somneuro Lab at UMass Amherst. She studies sleep and memory consolidation in infants and preschoolers. In her previous appointment at Temple University, she worked in the Developmental Science Lab under the advisement of Dr. Peter Marshall. She completed her doctoral degree at the Graduate Center in September 2021.
#
#### Her dissertation was an interdisciplinary investigation of infant sleep, discussing the methodologies of the field and linking sleep to motor development. 
#
#### Before graduate school, Dr. Horger attended Millersville University and then spent several years working at the Vista School in Hershey, PA. 

#
#

#### Her research interests include sensory, motor, and cognitive development and the role of sleep in these domains. 

#
#
#
# 
#
#

#### Outside of the lab, she enjoys going to concerts, traveling, hiking, and spending time with her pets, Harley (the dog) and Pickles (the cat). 

